This bothers me so much about C/C++ syntax.
    int* a, b;
should clearly declare two int pointers, not one int pointer and one int.<p>Stroustrup wrote something somewhere where he explained that 
    int* a;
is more appropriate for use in C++ because C++ is supposed to be more focused on types, and
    int * a;
is more appropriate for C because of something about C's philosophy, but I can't remember what. I wish they would have changed the syntax for C++, but I guess he couldn't have while still keeping C++ a superset of C.<p>edit: found it: <a href="http://www2.research.att.com/~bs/bs_faq2.html
